<br>
&quot;Hermes we need to talk.&quot; Apollo says,  grasping his arm pulling him from Dionysus.<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen, mon frére... and listen good, for I am afraid to tell this tale more than once.&quot; he paused, closing his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;I had a preminition. I was in Egypt and I traveled all the way back to tell you. I knew something was wrong, I could feel it in my bones. All I knew is that something was awry in the north. Where in the north, I did not know. What it was, that neither did I know. I chalked it up to being a large mortal squabble. But it was not. For brother I saw our dismal future. I saw the fall of the Olympians themselves if we do not act soon, if we do not apply immediate action. And no dear brother, no half baked schemes from mortal heroes. We need a well planned out plan of attack, for this evil ::he paused before giving the energy a name:: is greater than Father Zeus. Or atleast it will grow to be in the soon future. The thing...::he pauses again, regaining his haggard composure:: it feeds of the negative energies. All the negative thoughts we expell, all the negative acts, it grows stronger.&quot;<br>
<br>
He placed his hand on his brothers shoulder, his look of pure dread seemingly to seep into the eye's of Hermes. <br>
<br>
&quot;I fear that if something is not done soon, we will have a problem on our hands to great to do something about.&quot; <br>
<br>
He let go of Hermes and looked to the sky. Mother Earth herself, Gaia seemed to know of the impending darkness. The sky grew darker as clouds seemed to cover the sky. A million thoughts were running through his head. His family, was in danger, but more than that, his universe was in danger. Everything he was used to, everything he grew to love could change this very second. He closed his eyes, seeming to say 'Thank You' to no one. Surely if he said thank you, the universe would atleast know he was not taking advantage of his graced exsistance.<br>
<br>
&quot;Brother, you musn't tell anyone of what I just told you. Time is a extremely fragile thing. I will help to this cause with everything I am. I will alert the Council of Time of which I am leader to do all they can to delay the impending evil. I will appeal to them brother, it will be done. For the Hours they do my bidding, and I am sure the Seasons will be of great help. Trust in my power and in your own, for no one can give you more strength than you can give yourself.&quot; he pointed to Hermes's chest, as if to say all the power needed was located within him. As if the only way to beat this was if everyone believed in themselves, for anything was possible if one believed something to be true with his whole being.<br>
<br>
Apollo smiled to Hermes. He ruffled the boys hair laughing. He always found a way to lighten up the most dark of moments as if not by his obvious light aura, but by his inner optimism he was able to shake off anything negative. He soon pulled Hermes into a &quot;noogie&quot; ruffaling his hair further laughing. He soon though, released him with a smile<br>
<br>
&quot;Let us get started mon frére. For there is much to be done.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/6/01 10:27:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Crystals lit</span><hr size=1> The crystals within the antechamber began to glow.  The blue crystal had been lit for a while, but for the denizens of this realm, it had not been deemed urgent.  But now it had become more than a nuisance.  Order amongst chaos, and chaos amongst order.  What had once been a single snooper, had not spread to encompass others.  Now these creatures were in a frenzy, trying to cope with the new factors in the equation.<br>
<br>
The blue was lit, sure.  But a black and silver crystal had been lit also.  Then recently a purple and white had too.  Chittering loudly amongst themselves, the sound echoing throughout the room, it would be as if you  suddenly found yourself burried up to your neck in mealworms, and their incessant chittering driving you insane.<br>
<br>
Imps began to appear in the room.  Their amber eyes seemed to be floating in the midst of darkness.  They flew above the heads of the insectoids, waiting to do their duties.  The insect watchers started reguritating gelatinous balls, and then handed them to the imps.  The language of these creatures are indescipherable, but they made excellent spies.  They had developed a way to communicate with other species through their secretions.  Only those skilled in reading saliva would be able to understand.<br>
<br>
The imps disappeared into tiny vortexes of their own creations.  Delivering the news that it may be time to act, and soon.  Too many have gotten wind of their activities.<br>
