:<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ionysus, I think it would be best if you entered into Poseidon's realm.  I have not been given permission yet, and to this day, I have not been able to collect the souls that have been lost at sea.  But I believe that there is a lot to be found there, if you are able to.  <br>
<br>
The Hindus believe that the world actually rests upon a giant tortoise that is plodding through the universe.  I do not know if this is true, but from what I have gathered from the Tree, there is an old hobbit that does live deep within the Indian Ocean, where exactly I am not sure.  Supposedly he has deep ties with the Tortoise, what kind, I am again not sure.  But there are problems even before you can reach him.  I am sure <br>
Grunkar's minions are everywhere, so do not be surprised if you do meet up with them.  But the true challenge would be persuading the old hobbit to assist us.  You see, the Hindus believe in reincarnation, and that everything occurs cyclically.  That means that they believe what is happening now had transpired before.  Therefore he may not see the need to assist us because that would be interrupting the cycle.  It would be up to you.<br>
<br>
Apollo, you have to go to Egypt, where Nike seems to call home.  There you have to go to their underworld, ruled by their god, Osiris.  Osiris is actually more tempestuous than our own Hades.  But I believe, since you represent light, and therefore life, he has no reason not to at least admit your presence.  But again, be careful.  you will have to be judged first.  Your worthiness will be weighed against that of a feather.  If you are found unworthy, sinful, and therefore your soul is heavier than that of the feather, they may condemn you to eternal torture.  But because you are a god, you should have at least a fighting chance.  <br>
<br>
But remember both of you, you two are entering into the realms of other gods, and therefore your powers will not be as great as they are here.  While there, the deities that rule supreme will have greater control.  Therefore you will have to utilize more of your wits than your brawn.<br>
<br>
Dionysus, when you are in India.  You must ascertain whether or not Krungar has affected them yet, which I believe that he has.  I believe there is an object that the old hobbit knows about, with which Krungar needs to revive himself.  But once again, I am unsure what it may be.<br>
<br>
As for you, Apollo, your job is also similar, but different as well.  When in Egypt, you need to discover what it is Krungar is after.  There are multiple artifacts that Krungar wants or may need.  One that I know of is the feather with which Osiris weighs the souls of the recently departed.  He will not be too willing to part with the feather for if he does, he will not be able to admit any more souls into his kingdom.  Therefore he will guard it selfishly.  So even if you do not manage to obtain the feather, at least it will put Osiris on alert, and therefore prevent Krungar and his minions from obtaining the feather as well.  Krungar needs it, so that he may bypass his imprisonment in Tartarus.  If he can somehow utilize the feather's powers, thereby lightening the sins which burden his soul, then his sould will be able to leave Tartarus.  Once that happens, it opens up a path for his body to leave as well.<br>
<br>
But as I said, there are other artifacts in Africa, in fact throughout the entire planet that could be used.  Therefore I can't stress the urgency of the matter.  We do not have much time.  For every wall we put up against Krungar, another path has opened that we do not know about.  <br>
<br>
While you two are gone, I will interrogate this demon here, and then proceed with some of my other leads.  I pray that the next time we meet, we will have made greater strides in stopping Krungar.<br>
